Notes:

Three ways of embedding CSS
1)External-- making a styles.css file.
2)Inline-- using in html tags.
3)<style>-- writing a <style> tag inside the <head> tag.

Advantages of External file:
1)Can be used in different html files.

Document Object Model:
1)Structure by which the browser interprets the html file.
2)Any object on DOM is called an element.
3)Every element has two attributes :a) id b) class
id is for an individual.
class is for a group.

Inline overrides <style> overrides External.

Division of html pages:
1)<div> :Divides html pages into blocks.
2)<span> :Divides in part of lines.


Display-->
1)inline.
2)inline-block.
3)block.
